{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Quad Cortex MIDI Control\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Automate your Neural DSP Quad Cortex directly from the Reaper timeline using Regions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 How it works\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script triggers MIDI commands based on {\b Region names} using a simple prefix system:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Presets}: Use the default {\f1 #} prefix followed by the number (e.g., {\f1 #5} to load Preset 5).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Scenes}: Use the default {\f1 !S} prefix followed by the letter or number (e.g., {\f1 !SB} or {\f1 !S2} to switch Scenes).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The script monitors the playhead in real-time. As soon as a named region is reached, the corresponding MIDI command is sent to your Quad Cortex.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Documentation & Support\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For more information and support, visit the official repository: https://github.com/6wheels/reaper-quad-cortex-midi-control\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
